  "text": "All selected studies with behavioral tests reported functional improvement associated with the presence of the MS/SPION complex in ischemic area and neurorepair histological changes. The meta-analysis of these studies showed that MS/SPIONs were efficient for treatments, although few studies applied neurological score or behavior tests. Recent reviews [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] also observed therapeutic efficacy of stem cells in several preclinical models of stroke but recognized that many fundamental questions related to cell characterization, cell dosage, cell fate, biodistribution, safety indices, outcome measures, and so on are critical for the successful development of a cell product. The labeling process of stem cells with iron oxide could increase cytotoxicity, but improvement of in vivo homing and tracking image techniques of cells.",
